Temaku (short for TErminal MarKUp) is a small (single header & source file)
library that I use for a lot of my internal projects and scripts to easily
pretty print help/usage/version information on the terminal by typing simple
markdown formatted text without actually having to implement or import a
complicated parser for something like ROFF or Markdown.

See `example.c` for a quick example of how you might use temaku.

Temaku has the following markup features:

```
=HEADER
*bold*
/italic/
_underlined_
|alternative color| (usually dim)
%B bold %b
%I italic %i
%U underline %u
%A alternative color %a
%S strikethrough %s
%R reverse video %r
%F{red} foreground color %f
%K{blue} background color %k
%E Clear background until end of line (Useful for setting background color)
%L{www.example.com} hyperlinks %l
```
